headline: New Survey Finds Women Are Skipping Their OB/GYN Exams, Increasing Risks for Cervical Cancer
summary: BD (Becton, Dickinson and Company) (NYSE: BDX), a leading global medical technology company, today announced the results of a new survey, revealing that 72% of women in the United States have delayed having a gynecology visit, with many highlighting the need for greater convenience, comfort and ease for this critical cervical cancer screening process.
